Title: Beneath Us
Description: “Beneath Us” is a short film that points to specific aspects of white ignorance within a mixed race lesbian relationship and exposes certain social and family values that allow racism to thrive. Rooted in self reflection and taking cues from queer call out culture, the short video will use “subconscious subtitles” to describe and expose certain mechanisms that enable racism to casually exist in even the most intimate relationships.

Title: Focus Woman
Description: “Focus Woman” is a celebration of independent art house cinema and the tasks of a lone projectionist as well as an exploration of gendered workplace harassment through a feminist lens.

Title: August 2014
Description: A time capsule of when it became undeniable to most Americans that the gruesome violence black communities experience at the hands of American law enforcement is excessive and disproportionate to those of white communities. This short film hopes to mark the mass consciousness shift made possible by smart phones allowing millions of people to document their lives and share videos of their lived experiences on the internet.

Title: Olympia Story
Description: From the near silence and invisibility of late motherhood a resolute woman attempts to help a young stranger who also finds herself at the edge of existence.

Title: Two Beds
Description: A queer doppelganger couple fights the age-old battle between hetero-normative monogamy and poly-amorous adventure.
